Source: rule-engine-postgres
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ton That Vu <ttvuhm@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 11),
               postgresql-server-dev-16 | postgresql-server-dev-17,
               cargo,
               rustc (>= 1.75),
               cargo-pgrx (>= 0.16.1)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/KSD-CO/rule-engine-postgres
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/KSD-CO/rule-engine-postgres
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/KSD-CO/rule-engine-postgres.git

Package: postgresql-16-rule-engine
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, postgresql-16
Description: PostgreSQL 16 extension for rule engine with GRL syntax
 Production-ready PostgreSQL extension written in Rust that brings
 rule engine capabilities directly into your database. Execute complex
 business logic using the Grule Rule Language (GRL) syntax.
 .
 Features:
  - High performance compiled Rust code
  - Forward and backward chaining
  - Rule Repository with versioning and tagging
  - JSON/JSONB support
  - Health checks and monitoring
  - Error codes for debugging
  - Docker support

